<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-275-661  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 275 661.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Jan 23 1989 v35 n1742 p17(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>WD cutting workforce by 11 percent; cites slower growth. (WesternDigital Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Deagon, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Western Digital Corp announces that it will reduce its workforceby 11 percent through a combination of layoffs and attrition.andO;Most of the employees affected by the cost-cutting move areproduction and administrative personnel.andP;  The announcement followsthe voluntary departure of 400 employees from Western Digital'sdisk drive facilities in Singapore.andP;  The cuts are intended tobring manufacturing costs line with the company's reduced growthrate, and to improve cash flow.andP;  Western Digital cites a slowdownin the business of its secondary customers as the reason for thecompany's reduced growth.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Western Digital Corp. (layoffs).andO;Ticker:    WDC.andO;Topic:     LayoffCost ReductionComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>